        <num>CC 1581</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>SECTION 3.  OF THE COMPETENCE OF WITNESSES AND OF CERTAIN
DESIGNATIONS IN TESTAMENTS
Art. 1581.  Persons incompetent to be witnesses
A person cannot be a witness to any testament if the person is insane, blind, under the
age of sixteen, or unable to sign his name.</p>
        </content>
